page.title: 08Housing in Dalston
page.content: We did a survey to see which are the most common type of houses lived in,in Dalston today. Out of thirty three children in the class J1/2 three people lived in terraced houses and eight in semi-detached and fourteen in detached and last of all four live in link detached houses.Then we asked the same class whether they lived in cottages,houses,bungalows,flats or mansions.Three people live in cottages eighteen people live in houses , six people live in bungalows no_one lives in a flat and one person lives in a mansion.Then we asked them if they rented or owned thier house.Three people rented their house and twenty one people owned their houses.We asked the same questions and in J3 one person lived at the end of a terrace and no_one in J4 did.There were three people who lived in a (see page 20)
